WEBVTT

00:05.922 --> 00:07.465
{\an3}Sorry.

00:07.549 --> 00:08.967
Ten minutes isn't
officially late.

00:09.050 --> 00:10.760
I was early.

00:10.844 --> 00:12.470
{\an3}How early?
You already ate?

00:12.554 --> 00:13.805
I was hungry.

00:13.888 --> 00:16.099
Nat.

00:16.181 --> 00:18.101
{\an1}Two double espressos, please.
Make mine a single.

00:18.184 --> 00:19.602
Three cups of coffee?

00:19.686 --> 00:21.563
Two singles, please.

00:22.814 --> 00:24.274
Watching out for
my drug intake?

00:24.357 --> 00:25.775
I'm just being supportive.

00:25.859 --> 00:27.652
Okay, as long as
that's all it is.

00:27.736 --> 00:29.404
Promise.

00:29.487 --> 00:30.947
How's the old job hunt going?

00:31.030 --> 00:33.616
Terrible.
No one's interested.

00:33.700 --> 00:35.660
It's like they can't wait
to get me out the door.

00:35.744 --> 00:36.911
I can't believe this.
I mean, you created

00:36.995 --> 00:38.621
your own clothing line.
And stole

00:38.705 --> 00:39.497
someone else's concepts.

00:39.581 --> 00:41.291
{\an1}Only 'cause you were
taking too many pills.

00:41.374 --> 00:44.127
{\an3}Another reason why no one's
lining up to hire me.

00:44.210 --> 00:46.129
Listen to me.

00:46.212 --> 00:47.839
You got to keep trying.

00:49.591 --> 00:50.925
I appreciate your support.

00:51.009 --> 00:52.260
I really do.

00:52.343 --> 00:54.471
{\an3}But the fact
of the matter is,

00:54.554 --> 00:56.806
I threw away a really great job.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.725
Now, I may never
get hired again.

01:05.565 --> 01:07.692
What do you mean
I'm not getting the child?

01:07.776 --> 01:09.986
I told you when you applied
to be a foster mom

01:10.069 --> 01:12.155
that it would take time for
the application to be approved.

01:12.238 --> 01:13.656
But I found him.

01:13.740 --> 01:14.991
{\an1}Which is why the couple
getting custody

01:15.074 --> 01:16.493
want to thank you.

01:16.576 --> 01:17.994
But I saved his life.

01:18.077 --> 01:20.997
Yeah, you did, Kel,
but maybe it's time

01:21.080 --> 01:23.124
{\an1}to let him
get on with it.

01:24.375 --> 01:26.503
{\an1}Hi, I'm sorry to interrupt,
but we're here.

01:26.586 --> 01:29.506
Brandon, Kelly,
this is Kyle Vossler.

01:29.589 --> 01:30.840
{\an1}This is the foster parent
I told you about.

01:30.924 --> 01:32.550
{\an3}Congratulations.
Thanks.

01:32.634 --> 01:34.177
You, uh...

01:34.260 --> 01:35.720
you're my hero.

01:35.804 --> 01:37.806
{\an3}Well, I didn't
really do anything.

01:37.889 --> 01:39.516
No, no, you...

01:39.599 --> 01:41.601
Well, you just made
our lives complete.

01:41.684 --> 01:43.353
Hi.

01:45.063 --> 01:46.022
We named him Raphael.

01:46.105 --> 01:47.982
Raphael, that's a great name.

01:48.066 --> 01:49.359
{\an1}He was a,

01:49.442 --> 01:50.527
an angel wasn't he?

01:50.610 --> 01:51.903
KYLE:
Someday we just want

01:51.986 --> 01:54.531
{\an1}to be able to tell him
how he came to us.

01:54.614 --> 01:56.282
{\an4}MAN:
And we didn't want
to be talking about

01:56.366 --> 01:57.700
some mysterious Lady X.

01:57.784 --> 02:01.830
I thought that you were
just the foster parents.

02:02.997 --> 02:05.500
The county has
a fost-adopt program

02:05.583 --> 02:08.044
that allows foster parents
to apply for custody.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.380
{\an4}MAN:
But still, making it
this far is a huge win.

02:10.463 --> 02:12.882
The stories that we could tell
you about the approval process

02:12.966 --> 02:14.509
would just curl your hair.

02:15.927 --> 02:18.054
You know, the obstacles
that you guys had to overcome

02:18.137 --> 02:20.598
would probably make a great
story for my newspaper.

02:20.682 --> 02:22.517
{\an1}Please. Don't get
him started.

02:22.600 --> 02:24.269
{\an3}They actually had
to be convinced

02:24.352 --> 02:25.728
{\an3}that we could
nurture a child.

02:25.812 --> 02:27.564
{\an3}Can you?

02:31.276 --> 02:32.610
We came here
to thank you.

02:32.694 --> 02:34.237
I don't mean to offend you.

02:34.320 --> 02:36.614
My first concern is
for this baby.

02:37.866 --> 02:39.742
Our baby.

02:40.660 --> 02:42.579
How are you going to raise him?

02:42.662 --> 02:44.747
What, do you mean is he
going to be exposed

02:44.831 --> 02:46.583
to show tunes and makeup?

02:46.666 --> 02:48.459
Gene...
I think we should be going.

02:49.502 --> 02:50.795
You haven't answered
my question.

02:50.879 --> 02:53.006
We've answered questions
like yours for years.

02:54.132 --> 02:56.259
Now we have Raphael.

02:56.342 --> 02:57.886
We don't have to anymore.

